GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 1
SENATE BILL 567
Short Title: Medicaid SUD Services Rate Adjustment Act. (Public)
Sponsors: Senators Meyer, Adcock, and Batch (Primary Sponsors).
Referred to: Rules and Operations of the Senate
March 26, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO ESTABLISH AND ADJUST MEDICAID REIMBURSEMENT RATES FOR
3 SUBSTANCE USE DISORDER SERVICES.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. The Department of Health and Human Services, Division of Health
6 Benefits, shall make all of the following adjustments to the Medicaid Program:
7 (1) Increase rates paid for ASAM level 2.1 substance use intensive outpatient
8 program services to two hundred fifty-five dollars and twenty-eight cents
9 ($255.28) per diem.
10 (2) Increase the rates paid for ASAM level 2.5 substance use comprehensive
11 outpatient treatment program services to four hundred dollars ($400.00) per
12 diem.
13 (3) Establish coverage for ASAM level 3.1 clinically managed low-intensity
14 Residential Treatment services. A rate of three hundred fifty dollars ($350.00)
15 per diem shall be paid for these services.
16 (4) Establish coverage for ASAM level 3.3 clinically managed high-intensity
17 treatment services. A rate of two hundred fifty dollars ($250.00) per diem shall
18 be paid for these services.
19 (5) Establish coverage for ASAM level 3.5 clinically managed residential
20 treatment services. A rate of five hundred fifty dollars ($550.00) per diem
21 shall be paid for these services.
22 (6) Increase the rates paid for ASAM level 3.7 substance use medically monitored
23 community residential treatment services to six hundred fifty dollars
24 ($650.00) per diem.
25 (7) Increase the rates paid for ASAM level 3.7 non-hospital medical
26 detoxification services to seven hundred fifty-six dollars and sixty-five cents
27 ($756.65) per diem.
28 SECTION 2. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Department of
29 Health and Human Services, Division of Health Benefits, the sum of fifteen million dollars
30 ($15,000,000) in recurring funds for each year of the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium to be used to
31 effectuate the rate changes under this act. These funds shall provide a State match for
32 twenty-seven million four hundred thousand dollars ($27,400,000) in recurring federal funds for
33 each year of the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium, and those funds are appropriated to the Division of
34 Health Benefits for the same purpose.
35 SECTION 3. This act is effective July 1, 2025.
*S567-v-1*

